strings stretching from the th brane to the th brane; the
indices  are known as Chan-Paton indices.  Treating the fields
() as matrices, the analogue for multiple
branes of the Born-Infeld action () takes the form
 
This action is known as the nonabelian Born-Infeld action (NBI).  In
order to give a rigorous definition to the nonabelian Born-Infeld
action, it is necessary to resolve ordering ambiguities in the
expression ().  Since the spacetime coordinates 
associated with the D-brane positions in space-time become themselves
matrix-valued, even evaluating the pullbacks 
 involves resolving ordering issues.  Much work has
been done recently to resolve these ordering ambiguities (see
