The low-energy description of a system of  coincident flat D-branes
is thus given by  super Yang-Mills theory in the appropriate
dimension.  This connection between D-brane actions in string theory
and super Yang-Mills theory has led to many new developments,
including new insights into supersymmetric field theories, the
M(atrix) theory and AdS/CFT correspondences, and brane world
scenarios.

Branes from branes 

In this subsection we describe a remarkable feature of D-brane
systems, namely a mechanism by which one or more D-branes of a fixed
dimension can be used to construct additional D-branes of higher or
lower dimension.

